ested in previous studies, however our analysis suggests that these do not\nrepresent a distinct population. We examine the HR diagram of this set of high\nprobability wide binaries and find evidence for 980 over-luminous components\namong 2,227 K+K wide binaries; assuming these represent unresolved sub-systems,\nwe determine that the higher order multiplicity fraction for K+K wide systems\nis at least 39.6\\%.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Feb 2020 16:37:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-15"}
