we show that general\ninterval-decomposability does not admit such a local characterization, even\nwhen locality is understood in a broad sense. Our analysis focuses on the case\nof modules indexed over finite grids, the more general cases are left as future\nwork.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Feb 2020 17:46:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 26 Mar 2020 18:56:56 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 28 Jul 2020 07:36:32 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 4 Feb 2022 09:16:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-07"}
