y similar to Kerr images, once blurred to the EHT resolution. This implies\nthat a strong test of the Kerr spacetime may be out of reach with the current\ndata. We notice that future developments of the EHT could alter this situation.\nConclusions. Our results show the importance of studying alternatives to the\nKerr spacetime in order to be able to test the Kerr paradigm unambiguously.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Feb 2020 11:05:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 27 Oct 2020 08:19:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-03"}
