y up to a logarithmic factor in\n$d$. We show experimentally that our method yields practical improvements for\ncommon applications, relative to prior approaches.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Feb 2020 13:27:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 24 Feb 2020 14:33:28 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 6 Jul 2020 14:03:21 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 7 Apr 2021 15:50:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-08"}
